CatDescriptText: Mr. Ernest Wilson, 1854 Cliff Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1958, pg.2 with question: "Do people, whom you know, place more emphasis on social life than civic responsibilities?" answer reads: "I think that they place more on social rather than civic responsibilities."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Ernest Wilson, wearing multicolor plaid button down collared jacket with breast pockets, and dark hat, standing in front of light colored marble wall, between store windows displaying women's undergarments and men's dress shirts and neckties
